ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It is a comprehensive introduction to the modern-day physics centering around quantum effects in superconductivity, qubits, quantum-limited measurement, and other interesting novel subjects like nanomechanics. I would recommend this course to anybody interested in the field.

This course, especially the homework, is very challenging, especially for first-year students who had little past research experience in related fields. I will definitely recommend this course to students who are not first-year and not in related fields. But if they do choose it, even if their life will become harder, they will not regret it.
Must take unique course offered only at Yale

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: It provided necessary background and definitely helped with research.
It will be very much related to my future research in quantum information. It is really useful.
